<subSubSection id="C352B888AD4DFFEC2142F938FE1C27B4" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="532" pageId="1" pageNumber="530" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF7EB03AD4DFFEC2142F938FE1C27B4" blockId="1.[813,1451,1742,1913]" lastBlockId="3.[128,765,138,190]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="532" pageId="1" pageNumber="530">Diagnosis.—Anterolateral spine of carapace short, not reaching base of cornea; protogastric and epigastric lobes absent; extra-orbital sinus absent, rostrum triangular, deflected, carinate, outer proximal margin of movable finger of cheliped with lobe; palmar crest of cheliped subdisciform; anterior angle of ventral margin of epimeron 2 with modest scales; inner marginof ventral surface of ischium of cheliped with distal scaliform tubercle.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
